Umbraco Deployment Troubleshooting Report
We checked the deployment pipeline and confirmed that Azure DevOps is building and pushing the correct Docker image, and Alibaba ECI is pulling and running the latest image SHA correctly. From the infrastructure side the deployment process looks normal.
During the runtime inspection we noticed repeated application errors in the logs like:

"System.UriFormatException: Invalid URI: The hostname could not be parsed"
This usually indicates that the application is receiving an unexpected host or URL format from the reverse proxy layer.

Based on the current findings we recommend reviewing the following points:
In the nginx configuration, it may be useful to add the following header to ensure the backend receives the original host correctly:

proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Host $host;

In the deployment template (k8s/deploy-uat.yaml.template), the environment variable currently sets the application URL to localhost:

Umbraco_CMSWebRouting_UmbracoApplicationUrl: http://localhost:8080

Since the application is accessed through the UAT domain behind nginx, this value should probably reflect the actual public UAT URL instead of localhost.

These two areas are currently the most likely factors behind the issue and behavior observed after deployment







